<Layout 
  title="Medical Expenses | Compensation"
  description="Learn about coverage for medical expenses under the UK Armed Forces Compensation Scheme. Understand what treatments and services are covered and how to claim reimbursement.">
  <div class="container my-5">
    <h1 class="display-4 mb-4">Medical Expenses Coverage under AFCS</h1>
    <div class="row g-4">
      <div class="col-lg-8">
        <p class="lead">The Armed Forces Compensation Scheme (AFCS) provides coverage for various medical expenses related to service-induced injuries or illnesses. This page outlines what medical expenses are covered and how to claim reimbursement.</p>
        
        <h2 class="h3 mt-4">Covered Medical Expenses</h2>
        <p>The AFCS can cover a range of medical expenses, including:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Costs of ongoing medical treatment</li>
          <li>Prescription medications</li>
          <li>Specialist consultations</li>
          <li>Physiotherapy and rehabilitation services</li>
          <li>Mental health treatments</li>
          <li>Medical equipment and aids</li>
        </ul>
        
        <h2 class="h3 mt-4">Eligibility for Medical Expense Coverage</h2>
        <p>To be eligible for medical expense coverage:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>The treatment must be for a condition caused or worsened by service</li>
          <li>The expense must not be covered by the NHS or other government schemes</li>
          <li>The treatment must be deemed medically necessary</li>
        </ul>
        
        <h2 class="h3 mt-4">Claiming Reimbursement</h2>
        <p>To claim reimbursement for medical expenses:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Keep all receipts and invoices for medical treatments</li>
          <li>Obtain a letter from your doctor confirming the necessity of the treatment</li>
          <li>Submit a claim form along with supporting documentation</li>
          <li>Claims should be submitted as soon as possible after incurring the expense</li>
        </ul>
        
        <h2 class="h3 mt-4">Travel Expenses</h2>
        <p>The AFCS may also cover travel expenses related to medical treatment:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Travel costs to and from medical appointments</li>
          <li>Accommodation expenses if treatment requires overnight stays</li>
          <li>Mileage allowance for use of private vehicles</li>
        </ul>
        
        <h2 class="h3 mt-4">Ongoing and Future Medical Needs</h2>
        <p>For long-term or complex medical needs:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>A care needs assessment may be conducted</li>
          <li>A personalised care plan can be developed</li>
          <li>Regular reviews ensure ongoing needs are met</li>
        </ul>
        
        <h2 class="h3 mt-4">Limitations and Exclusions</h2>
        <p>Be aware of certain limitations:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Experimental or non-conventional treatments may not be covered</li>
          <li>Cosmetic procedures are generally not eligible unless directly related to service injury</li>
          <li>There may be caps on certain types of expenses</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="col-lg-4">
        <div class="card bg-light mb-4">
          <div class="card-body">
            <h3 class="h5">Related Information</h3>
            <ul class="list-unstyled">
              <li><a href="/medical/long-term-care" class="text-decoration-none">Long-term Care</a></li>
              <li><a href="/medical/rehabilitation" class="text-decoration-none">Rehabilitation Services</a></li>
              <li><a href="/financial/budgeting" class="text-decoration-none">Financial Planning</a></li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="card mb-4">
          <div class="card-body">
            <h3 class="h5">Expense Claim Form</h3>
            <p>Download and complete our medical expense claim form to request reimbursement.</p>
            <a href="/expense-claim-form" class="btn btn-primary">Download Form</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
